revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Sector_SetWind}} {{Special|218|tag, amount, angle, useline|Sector|Wind}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''amount'': Strength of the wind * ''angle'': Angle the wind blows * ''useline'': Get strength and angle from the line instead?
If ''useline'' is 1, this behaves just like BOOM's 224 linedef. If ''useline'' is 0, then the magnitude and angle parameters are used instead of the size and orientation of the line.
If used in a script, keep in mind that the sector needs the "pusher/puller/wind enabled" [[sector specials|flag]] (4096) for this to have an effect.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as : {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Boom}} 224:Set Wind || Sector_SetWind (tag, 0, 0, 1) || |- |{{icon|Eternity}} 293:TransferHereticWind || Sector_SetWind (tag, 0, 0, 1) || |}
